## Step 1: Write the formula for combinations
$\dbinom{n}{k} = \dfrac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}$
## Step 2: Plug in n=22 and k=19 into the combination formula
$\dbinom{22}{19} = \dfrac{22!}{19!(22-19)!}$
## Step 3: Simplify the factorial terms
$\dbinom{22}{19} = \dfrac{22!}{19!3!}$
## Step 4: Simplify the expression by canceling out common factors in the numerator and denominator
$\dbinom{22}{19} = \dfrac{22 \times 21 \times 20 \times 19!}{19! \times 3 \times 2 \times 1}$
## Step 5: Cancel out the common factors and simplify
$\dbinom{22}{19} = \dfrac{22 \times 21 \times 20}{3 \times 2 \times 1}$
## Step 6: Perform the multiplication in the numerator and denominator
$\dbinom{22}{19} = \dfrac{9240}{6}$
## Step 7: Perform the division
$\dbinom{22}{19} = 1540$
